# nyne-navigate — Scoped Reading & Exploration

Efficient code navigation through nyne's virtual filesystem. Every recognized source file
gains an `@/` namespace containing its decomposed structure. Use these virtual paths instead
of reading raw files — scoped reads return only the relevant code, saving ~90% of context tokens.

## Core Principle: Never Read Raw Source Files

Reading a 400-line file to find a 25-line function wastes 94% of consumed tokens. Always
use the VFS decomposition — the rules and path conventions below are the canonical source.

